        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I'm not really sure this behavior can be considered a bug, it might be an improvements or an additional feature.\nBTW, here's the issue.\n\nSometimes HTTP request returns a particular response header called \"Refresh:\".\nConsider this case\n\n{code}\nHTTP 200\nDate: Mon, 28 May 2007 20:50:24 GMT\nServer: Apache\/1.3.37 (Unix) mod_auth_passthrough\/1.8 mod_log_bytes\/1.2 mod_bwlimited\/1.4 PHP\/4.4.4 FrontPage\/5.0.2.2635.SR1.2 mod_ssl\/2.8.28 OpenSSL\/0.9.8a\nX-powered-by: PHP\/4.4.4\nRefresh: 0; url=account-login.php?returnto=%2Ftorrents-details.php%3Fid%3D1797\nConnection: close\n{code}\n\nIf you try to open this URL in a browser it will be immediatly redirected to url=account-login.php?returnto=%2Ftorrents-details.php%3Fid%3D1797 .\nShould Zend_Http_Client follow this responses a redirect?"
        },
